uriParameters.Name: $filter
uriParameters.Description: Equality operators relating to searching user entitlements seperated by and clauses. Valid filters include: licenseId, licenseStatus, userType, and name. licenseId: filters based on license assignment using license names. i.e. licenseId eq 'Account-Stakeholder' or licenseId eq 'Account-Express'. licenseStatus: filters based on license status. currently only supports disabled. i.e. licenseStatus eq 'Disabled'. To get disabled basic licenses, you would pass (licenseId eq 'Account-Express' and licenseStatus eq 'Disabled') userType: filters off identity type. Suppored types are member or guest i.e. userType eq 'member'. name: filters on if the user's display name or email contians given input. i.e. get all users with "test" in email or displayname is "name eq 'test'". A valid query could be: (licenseId eq 'Account-Stakeholder' or (licenseId eq 'Account-Express' and licenseStatus eq 'Disabled')) and name eq 'test' and userType eq 'guest'.

uriParameters.Name: $orderBy
uriParameters.Description: PropertyName and Order (separated by a space ( )) to sort on (e.g. lastAccessed desc). Order defaults to ascending. valid properties to order by are dateCreated, lastAccessed, and name

uriParameters.Description: Continuation token for getting the next page of data set. If null is passed, gets the first page.

uriParameters.Description: Comma (",") separated list of properties to select in the result entitlements. names of the properties are - 'Projects, 'Extensions' and 'Grouprules'.

Models.Name: Contribution

Properties.Name: constraints
Properties.Description: List of constraints (filters) that should be applied to the availability of this contribution

Properties.Name: description
Properties.Description: Description of the contribution/type

Properties.Name: id
Properties.Description: Fully qualified identifier of the contribution/type

Properties.Description: Includes is a set of contributions that should have this contribution included in their targets list.

Properties.Description: Properties/attributes of this contribution

Properties.Name: restrictedTo
Properties.Description: List of demanded claims in order for the user to see this contribution (like anonymous, public, member...).

Properties.Name: targets
Properties.Description: The ids of the contribution(s) that this contribution targets. (parent contributions)

Properties.Name: type
Properties.Description: Id of the Contribution Type

Properties.Name: visibleTo
Properties.Description: VisibleTo can be used to restrict whom can reference a given contribution/type. This value should be a list of publishers or extensions access is restricted too.  Examples: "ms" - Means only the "ms" publisher can reference this. "ms.vss-web" - Means only the "vss-web" extension from the "ms" publisher can reference this.

Models.Name: ContributionConstraint
Models.Description: Specifies a constraint that can be used to dynamically include/exclude a given contribution

Properties.Name: group
Properties.Description: An optional property that can be specified to group constraints together. All constraints within a group are AND'd together (all must be evaluate to True in order for the contribution to be included). Different groups of constraints are OR'd (only one group needs to evaluate to True for the contribution to be included).

Properties.Name: id
Properties.Description: Fully qualified identifier of a shared constraint

Properties.Name: inverse
Properties.Description: If true, negate the result of the filter (include the contribution if the applied filter returns false instead of true)

Properties.Name: name
Properties.Description: Name of the IContributionFilter plugin

Properties.Name: properties
Properties.Description: Properties that are fed to the contribution filter class

Properties.Name: relationships
Properties.Description: Constraints can be optionally be applied to one or more of the relationships defined in the contribution. If no relationships are defined then all relationships are associated with the constraint. This means the default behaviour will eliminate the contribution from the tree completely if the constraint is applied.

Models.Name: ContributionLicensingBehaviorType
Models.Description: How the inclusion of this contribution should change based on licensing

Properties.Name: alwaysInclude
Properties.Description: Always include the contribution regardless of whether or not the user is licensed for the extension

Properties.Name: onlyIfLicensed
Properties.Description: Default value - only include the contribution if the user is licensed for the extension

Properties.Name: onlyIfUnlicensed
Properties.Description: Only include the contribution if the user is NOT licensed for the extension

Properties.Description: The type of failure (if any) of the pull request merge.

Properties.Description: The ID of the job used to run the pull request merge. Used internally.

Properties.Description: Options used when the pull request merge runs. These are separate from completion options since completion happens only once and a new merge will run every time the source branch of the pull request changes.

Properties.Description: The current status of the pull request merge.

Properties.Description: The ID of the pull request.

Properties.Description: Used internally.

Properties.Description: If true, this pull request supports multiple iterations. Iteration support means individual pushes to the source branch of the pull request can be reviewed and comments left in one iteration will be tracked across future iterations.

Properties.Name: targetRefName
Properties.Description: The name of the target branch of the pull request.

Properties.Description: The title of the pull request.

Properties.Name: url
Properties.Description: Used internally.

Properties.Description: Any work item references associated with this pull request.

Models.Name: GitPullRequestCompletionOptions
Models.Description: Preferences about how the pull request should be completed.

Properties.Name: autoCompleteIgnoreConfigIds
Properties.Description: List of any policy configuration Id's which auto-complete should not wait for. Only applies to optional policies (isBlocking == false). Auto-complete always waits for required policies (isBlocking == true).

Properties.Name: bypassPolicy
Properties.Description: If true, policies will be explicitly bypassed while the pull request is completed.

Properties.Name: bypassReason
Properties.Description: If policies are bypassed, this reason is stored as to why bypass was used.

Properties.Name: deleteSourceBranch
Properties.Description: If true, the source branch of the pull request will be deleted after completion.

Properties.Name: mergeCommitMessage
Properties.Description: If set, this will be used as the commit message of the merge commit.

Properties.Name: mergeStrategy
Properties.Description: Specify the strategy used to merge the pull request during completion. If MergeStrategy is not set to any value, a no-FF merge will be created if SquashMerge == false. If MergeStrategy is not set to any value, the pull request commits will be squashed if SquashMerge == true. The SquashMerge property is deprecated. It is recommended that you explicitly set MergeStrategy in all cases. If an explicit value is provided for MergeStrategy, the SquashMerge property will be ignored.

Properties.Name: squashMerge
Properties.Description: SquashMerge is deprecated. You should explicitly set the value of MergeStrategy. If MergeStrategy is set to any value, the SquashMerge value will be ignored. If MergeStrategy is not set, the merge strategy will be no-fast-forward if this flag is false, or squash if true.

Properties.Name: transitionWorkItems
Properties.Description: If true, we will attempt to transition any work items linked to the pull request into the next logical state (i.e. Active -> Resolved)

Properties.Name: triggeredByAutoComplete
Properties.Description: If true, the current completion attempt was triggered via auto-complete. Used internally.

Models.Name: GitPullRequestMergeOptions
Models.Description: The options which are used when a pull request merge is created.

Properties.Name: conflictAuthorshipCommits
Properties.Description: If true, conflict resolutions applied during the merge will be put in separate commits to preserve authorship info for git blame, etc.

Properties.Name: disableRenames
Properties.Description: If true, rename detection will not be performed during the merge.

Models.Name: GitPullRequestMergeStrategy
Models.Description: Specify the strategy used to merge the pull request during completion. If MergeStrategy is not set to any value, a no-FF merge will be created if SquashMerge == false. If MergeStrategy is not set to any value, the pull request commits will be squashed if SquashMerge == true. The SquashMerge property is deprecated. It is recommended that you explicitly set MergeStrategy in all cases. If an explicit value is provided for MergeStrategy, the SquashMerge property will be ignored.

Properties.Name: noFastForward
Properties.Description: A two-parent, no-fast-forward merge. The source branch is unchanged. This is the default behavior.

Properties.Name: rebase
Properties.Description: Rebase the source branch on top of the target branch HEAD commit, and fast-forward the target branch. The source branch is updated during the rebase operation.

Properties.Name: rebaseMerge
Properties.Description: Rebase the source branch on top of the target branch HEAD commit, and create a two-parent, no-fast-forward merge. The source branch is updated during the rebase operation.

Properties.Name: squash
Properties.Description: Put all changes from the pull request into a single-parent commit.

Properties.Description: Indicates that the ref update request could not be completed because part of the graph would be disconnected by this change, and the caller does not have ForcePush permission on the repository.

Properties.Name: refNameConflict
Properties.Description: The ref update could not be completed because, in case-insensitive mode, the ref name conflicts with an existing, differently-cased ref name.

Properties.Name: rejectedByPlugin
Properties.Description: The ref update could not be completed because it was rejected by the plugin.

Properties.Name: rejectedByPolicy
Properties.Description: The ref update could not be completed because it was rejected by policy.

Properties.Name: staleOldObjectId
Properties.Description: Indicates that the ref update request could not be completed because the old object ID presented in the request was not the object ID of the ref when the database attempted the update. The most likely scenario is that the caller lost a race to update the ref.

Properties.Name: succeeded
Properties.Description: Indicates that the ref update request was completed successfully.

Properties.Name: succeededCorruptRef
Properties.Description: Indicates that the ref update request was completed successfully, but the passed-in ref was corrupt - as in, the old object ID was bad.  This should only happen during deletes.

Properties.Name: succeededNonExistentRef
Properties.Description: Indicates that the ref update request was completed successfully, but the ref doesn't actually exist so no changes were made.  This should only happen during deletes.

Properties.Name: unprocessed
Properties.Description: The request was not processed

Properties.Name: unresolvableToCommit
Properties.Description: The ref update request could not be completed because the new object ID for the ref could not be resolved to a commit object (potentially through any number of tags)

Properties.Name: writePermissionRequired
Properties.Description: The ref update request could not be completed because the user lacks write permissions required to write this ref

For example, a subscription scoped to project A will not produce notifications for events published from project B.

Properties.Name: effectiveAllow
Properties.Description: This is the combination of all of the explicit and inherited permissions for this identity on this token.  These are the permissions used when determining if a given user has permission to perform an action.

Properties.Name: effectiveDeny
Properties.Description: This is the combination of all of the explicit and inherited permissions for this identity on this token.  These are the permissions used when determining if a given user has permission to perform an action.

Properties.Name: inheritedAllow
Properties.Description: These are the permissions that are inherited for this identity on this token.  If the token does not inherit permissions this will be 0.  Note that any permissions that have been explicitly set on this token for this identity, or any groups that this identity is a part of, are not included here.

Properties.Name: inheritedDeny
Properties.Description: These are the permissions that are inherited for this identity on this token.  If the token does not inherit permissions this will be 0.  Note that any permissions that have been explicitly set on this token for this identity, or any groups that this identity is a part of, are not included here.

Note: 1) It is represented in Hexadecimal format with 8 digits for a step. 2) Internally, the step ID value for first step starts with 2 so actionPath = 00000002 step 9, will have an ID = 10 and actionPath = 0000000a step 15, will have an ID =16 and actionPath = 00000010 3) actionPath of shared step is concatenated with the parent step of test case. Example, it would be something of type -  0000000300000001 where 00000003 denotes action path of test step and 00000001 denotes action path for shared step

Properties.Name: copyFromClock
Properties.Description: Set the value from clock.

Properties.Name: copyFromCurrentUser
Properties.Description: Set the current user to the target field. Example : {"actionType":"$copyFromCurrentUser","targetField":"System.AssignedTo","value":""}.

Properties.Name: copyFromField
Properties.Description: Copy the value from a specified field and set to target field. Example : {actionType: "$copyFromField", targetField: "System.AssignedTo", value:"System.ChangedBy"}. Here, value is copied from "System.ChangedBy" and set to "System.AssingedTo" field.

Properties.Name: copyFromServerClock
Properties.Description: Use the current time to set the value of the target field. Example : {actionType: "$copyFromServerClock", targetField: "System.CreatedDate", value: ""}

Properties.Name: copyFromServerCurrentUser
Properties.Description: Use the current user to set the value of the target field.

Properties.Name: copyValue
Properties.Description: Set the value of target field to given value. Example : {actionType: "$copyValue", targetField: "ScrumInherited.mypicklist", value: "samplevalue"}

Properties.Name: disallowValue
Properties.Description: Disallows a field from being set to a specific value.

Properties.Name: hideTargetField
Properties.Description: Hides target field from the form. This is a server side only action.

Properties.Name: makeReadOnly
Properties.Description: Make the target field read-only. Example : {"actionType":"$makeReadOnly","targetField":"Microsoft.VSTS.Common.Activity","value":""}

Properties.Name: makeRequired
Properties.Description: Make the target field required. Example : {"actionType":"$makeRequired","targetField":"Microsoft.VSTS.Common.Activity","value":""}

Properties.Name: setDefaultFromClock
Properties.Description: Set the default value on the target field from server clock. This is used if user creates the field like Date/Time and uses default value.

Properties.Name: setDefaultFromCurrentUser
Properties.Description: Set the default current user value on the target field. This is used if the user creates the field of type identity and uses default value.

Properties.Name: setDefaultFromField
Properties.Description: Set the default value on from existing field to the target field.  This used wants to set a existing field value to the current field.

Properties.Name: setDefaultValue
Properties.Description: Set a default value on the target field. This is used if the user creates a integer/string field and sets a default value of this field.

Properties.Name: setValueToEmpty
Properties.Description: Set the value of the target field to empty.

Models.Name: RuleCondition
Models.Description: Defines a condition on a field when the rule should be triggered.

Properties.Name: conditionType
Properties.Description: Type of condition. $When. This condition limits the execution of its children to cases when another field has a particular value, i.e. when the Is value of the referenced field is equal to the given literal value. $WhenNot.This condition limits the execution of its children to cases when another field does not have a particular value, i.e.when the Is value of the referenced field is not equal to the given literal value. $WhenChanged.This condition limits the execution of its children to cases when another field has changed, i.e.when the Is value of the referenced field is not equal to the Was value of that field. $WhenNotChanged.This condition limits the execution of its children to cases when another field has not changed, i.e.when the Is value of the referenced field is equal to the Was value of that field.

Properties.Description: Field that defines condition.

Properties.Description: Value of field to define the condition for rule.
